Just like Tern.js, would be nice if Intellisense could recognize JavaScript prototypal inheritance, as suggested in [UserVoice](https://visualstudio.uservoice.com/forums/293070-visual-studio-code/suggestions/9535698-js-intellisense-based-on-prototype-methods).

Despite of multi-file injections (most times discovered only in runtime), static analysis is enough to solve single-file cases like in this example:

```
function MyThing() {
    // ...
}

MyThing.prototype.example = function () {
    // ...
};

var thing = new MyThing();
thing. // should suggest "example"
```
